Implement the missing StrictMode guard in /app/frontend/src/components/common/HeroChatDemo.tsx. Suggested fix: add a useRef flag and early-return on second effect run, e.g.:

  const seededRef = useRef(false);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (seededRef.current) return;
    seededRef.current = true;
    const reply = CANNED.leave;
    streamAssistant(reply.text, reply.citation, reply.portals);
  }, []);

After the fix, the assistant message count after mount must be exactly 1 (not 2).
